{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it came to pass, that, as he was praying in a certain place, when he ceased,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.",
          "speaker": "Disciple"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "When ye pray, say,",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he was casting out a devil, and it was dumb. And it came to pass, when the devil was gone out, the dumb spake; and the people wondered."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Casts Out a Demon"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "He casteth out devils through Beelzebub the chief of the devils.",
          "speaker": "Some people"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And others, tempting him, sought of him a sign from heaven."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it came to pass, as he spake these things,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the paps which thou hast sucked.",
          "speaker": "A certain woman"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "A Woman Praises Jesus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when the people were gathered thick together, he began to say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "sermon",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Sign of Jonah"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And as he spake, a certain Pharisee besought him to dine with him: and he went in, and sat down to meat."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Woes to the Pharisees"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when the Pharisee saw it, he marvelled that he had not first washed before dinner."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the Lord said unto him,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Master, thus saying thou reproachest us also.",
          "speaker": "One of the lawyers"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Woes to the Lawyers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 46,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 53,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And as he said these things unto them, the scribes and the Pharisees began to urge him vehemently, and to provoke him to speak of many things:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 54,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Laying wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth, that they might accuse him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}